{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841769569,"sessionID":"ses_287966bbfffe2VsyxS7EkLSpMJ","part":{"id":"prt_d786a19b8001m7Ho78dass61MJ","messageID":"msg_d7869f5e9001xp7UyGo8pp7mgz","sessionID":"ses_287966bbfffe2VsyxS7EkLSpMJ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-003  \n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n\nExtract shared types and constants from AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD definitions to reduce code duplication and establish a common type foundation for the runtime API group.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Shared Phase Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a common `SandboxPhase` type to represent the lifecycle phase of sandbox-based resources, replacing the individual phase types in AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxPhase type is defined\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxPhase` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `Pending`, `Running`, `Succeeded`, `Failed`, `Unknown`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxPhase constants are defined\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n- **THEN** it SHALL define the following constants:\n  - `SandboxPhasePending`\n  - `SandboxPhaseRunning`\n  - `SandboxPhaseSucceeded`\n  - `SandboxPhaseFailed`\n  - `SandboxPhaseUnknown`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxPhase\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct in `agentruntime_types.go`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Phase` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxPhase` instead of `AgentRuntimePhase`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxPhase values match legacy AgentRuntimePhase\n- **GIVEN** the `SandboxPhase` type and constants\n- **WHEN** comparing to legacy `AgentRuntimePhase` values\n- **THEN** the string values SHALL match exactly (e.g., `SandboxPhasePending` = \"Pending\")\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Shared Condition Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a common `SandboxConditionType` type for conditions that apply to both AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxConditionType type is defined\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxConditionType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxConditionType constants are defined\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n- **THEN** it SHALL define the following constants:\n  - `SandboxConditionReady` — indicates the resource is ready to accept requests\n  - `SandboxConditionSandboxCreated` — indicates the sandbox has been created\n  - `SandboxConditionSandboxReady` — indicates the sandbox is ready for use\n  - `SandboxConditionFailed` — indicates the resource has failed\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxConditionType\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeCondition` struct in `agentruntime_types.go`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Type` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxConditionType` instead of `AgentRuntimeConditionType`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses SandboxConditionType\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterCondition` struct in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Type` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `SandboxConditionType` instead of `CodeInterpreterConditionType`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Shared Condition Struct Definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a common `SandboxCondition` struct to represent conditions for sandbox-based resources.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxCondition struct is defined\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the struct definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `SandboxCondition` struct with the following fields:\n  - `Type` (`SandboxConditionType`, required)\n  - `Status` (`corev1.ConditionStatus`, required, enum: True, False, Unknown)\n  - `LastTransitionTime` (`metav1.Time`, optional)\n  - `Reason` (string, optional)\n  - `Message` (string, optional)\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime uses SandboxCondition\n- **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Conditions` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL be of type `[]SandboxCondition` instead of `[]AgentRuntimeCondition`\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses SandboxCondition\n- **GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterStatus` struct\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Conditions` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL be of type `[]SandboxCondition` instead of `[]CodeInterpreterCondition`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Shared Protocol Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL retain the existing `ProtocolType` definition in the shared types file for use by resources that need protocol specifications.\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType is preserved\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `ProtocolType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `HTTP`, `HTTPS`\n\n#### Scenario: ProtocolType constants are preserved\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `ProtocolHTTP` and `ProtocolHTTPS` constants\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort uses ProtocolType\n- **GIVEN** the `TargetPort` struct in `codeinterpreter_types.go`\n- **WHEN** inspecting the `Protocol` field\n- **THEN** it SHALL continue to use `ProtocolType`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Shared AuthMode Type Definition\n\nThe system SHALL retain the existing `AuthModeType` definition in the shared types file for authentication mode specifications.\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType is preserved\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain an `AuthModeType` string type with kubebuilder validation enum: `picod`, `none`\n\n#### Scenario: AuthModeType constants are preserved\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants\n- **THEN** it SHALL define `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` constants\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Shared TargetPort Struct Definition\n\nThe system SHALL retain the existing `TargetPort` struct definition for port configuration.\n\n#### Scenario: TargetPort struct is preserved\n- **GIVEN** the shared types file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the struct definitions\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `TargetPort` struct with the following fields:\n  - `PathPrefix` (string, optional)\n  - `Name` (string, optional)\n  - `Port` (uint32, required, minimum 1, maximum 65535)\n  - `Protocol` (`ProtocolType`, optional, default \"HTTP\")\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Legacy Type Aliases for Backward Compatibility\n\nThe system SHALL provide type aliases in individual CRD type files to maintain backward compatibility during the transition period.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimePhase is aliased\n- **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimePhase = SandboxPhase`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeConditionType is aliased\n- **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimeConditionType = SandboxConditionType`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeCondition is aliased\n- **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type definitions after refactoring\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a type alias: `type AgentRuntimeCondition = SandboxCondition`\n\n#### Scenario: Legacy constants are aliased\n- **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the constants after refactoring\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain constant aliases for backward compatibility (e.g., `const AgentRuntimePhasePending = SandboxPhasePending`)\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter uses shared types directly\n- **GIVEN** the `codeinterpreter_types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the type usage\n- **THEN** it SHALL use shared types directly without duplication (no need for aliases since CodeInterpreter was already aligned with shared patterns)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Package Structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize shared types in a dedicated file within the API package.\n\n#### Scenario: Types file exists\n- **GIVEN** the package `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain a `types.go` file for shared type definitions\n\n#### Scenario: Types file has package documentation\n- **GIVEN** the `types.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the file header\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain appropriate package documentation comments explaining the shared types purpose\n\n#### Scenario: Original files import shared types\n- **GIVEN** the `agentruntime_types.go` and `codeinterpreter_types.go` files\n- **WHEN** inspecting the imports\n- **THEN** no additional imports SHALL be needed since shared types are in the same package\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeepCopy Generation\n\nThe system SHALL ensure DeepCopy methods are generated correctly for all shared types.\n\n#### Scenario: Shared types have DeepCopy methods\n- **GIVEN** the generated `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the generated code\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopy`, and `DeepCopyObject` methods for `SandboxCondition`\n\n#### Scenario: Legacy types reuse shared DeepCopy\n- **GIVEN** the generated `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` file\n- **WHEN** inspecting the generated code for legacy types\n- **THEN** type aliases SHALL reuse the DeepCopy methods from their underlying shared types\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Code Compilation\n\nThe system SHALL compile successfully after the refactoring.\n\n#### Scenario: Package compiles after refactoring\n- **GIVEN** a clean Go module at repository root\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `go build ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...`\n- **THEN** the package SHALL compile without errors\n\n#### Scenario: Tests pass after refactoring\n- **GIVEN** the existing test files in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...`\n- **THEN** all tests SHALL pass\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | NEW: Shared type definitions (SandboxPhase, SandboxConditionType, SandboxCondition, ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort) |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` | MODIFIED: Use shared types, add type aliases for backward compatibility |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` | MODIFIED: Remove duplicate type definitions, use shared types |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | GENERATED: Updated DeepCopy methods for shared types |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `k8s.io/api/core/v1` — Kubernetes core types (ConditionStatus)\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` — Kubernetes metadata types (Time)\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` — Runtime.Object interface (implicit via type usage)\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Type aliases (`type X = Y`) provide compile-time equivalence, allowing existing code to continue working without modification\n- Shared types follow the \"Sandbox\" naming convention to indicate they apply to sandbox-based resources\n- The refactoring reduces code duplication while maintaining full backward compatibility\n- Future CRDs for sandbox-based resources can reuse these shared types\n- All kubebuilder markers (validation, default values) SHALL be preserved on the shared type definitions\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775841769534,"end":1775841769566}}}}
