{"type":"text","timestamp":1775841786390,"sessionID":"ses_287966bbfffe2VsyxS7EkLSpMJ","part":{"id":"prt_d786b24d40016JEZ193THyod7L","messageID":"msg_d786af893001GUxz4vYZbDKuM1","sessionID":"ses_287966bbfffe2VsyxS7EkLSpMJ","type":"text","text":"Done! I've written the `delta-spec.md` file for **AR-003 — CRD Shared Types and Constants**.\n\nThe spec defines requirements for extracting shared types from AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs to reduce code duplication:\n\n**Key Requirements:**\n1. **SandboxPhase** - Shared phase type (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n2. **SandboxConditionType** - Shared condition type constants (Ready, SandboxCreated, SandboxReady, Failed)\n3. **SandboxCondition** - Shared condition struct with Type, Status, LastTransitionTime, Reason, Message\n4. **ProtocolType & AuthModeType** - Retained shared types\n5. **TargetPort** - Shared struct for port configuration\n6. **Backward Compatibility** - Type aliases (e.g., `type AgentRuntimePhase = SandboxPhase`)\n\n**New/Modified Files:**\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` — NEW file for shared types\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` — MODIFIED with type aliases\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` — MODIFIED to use shared types\n\nEach requirement includes GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios as specified in the OpenSpec format.","time":{"start":1775841786388,"end":1775841786388}}}
